#
# 0000: Wait for one cycle (NOP). The rest of the trace instruction is ignored.
#
# 0001: Send data. The rest of the trace instruction instruction is the data.
#
# 0010: Receive data. The input data is compared with the rest of the trace instruction.
#
# 0011: Assert trace replay’s “done_o” signal. The rest of the trace is ignored. 
#
# 0100: Finish simulation. The reset of the trace instruction is ignored.
#
# 0101: Wait for a cycle counter to reach 0. The rest of the trace instruction is ignored.
#
# 0110: Set cycle counter. The rest of the trace (or the lowest 16-bits if there are more 
#       than 16-bits) will be the value the cycle counter is set to. Every cycle, the cycle 
#       counter will decrease by 1. When used in conjunction with command 5, you can wait 
#       for a specific number of cycles.
#
